<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1255" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1255">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.2311/31.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretaries of the Treasury, of Commerce and
                                    Labor, and of War</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Identic telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-10">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 10, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>This Department’s telegram of the 8th instant. The Governor of Texas has
                            been informed that the Mexican troops in question are to be used for
                            general hostilities in the State of Chihuahua and has accordingly seen
                            fit to withdraw his consent to their passage over Texan territory, and
                            has so informed this Department. I must consequently cancel my request
                            that your Department render assistance in the matter and say instead
                            that I will appreciate it if you will promptly cancel any orders that
                            have already been given and see that nothing further is done.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>